  <notes>
    Completed 2026-06-29 by Wave 3 autonomous dispatch (task-execute, FULL rigor).

    Refactor summary:
    - Sole SemanticSearch consumer of `useDocumentActions` is `App.tsx` line 367
      (SearchCommandBar.tsx receives handlers as props — no direct hook use).
      Verified by grep across `src/client/code-pages/SemanticSearch/` BEFORE
      editing per POML constraint.
    - Updated `App.tsx` import from `./hooks/useDocumentActions` to
      `@spaarke/document-operations`; added `getBffBaseUrl()` import from
      local `./services/apiBase`; call site changed to
      `useDocumentActions({ bffBaseUrl: getBffBaseUrl() })`.
    - Deleted the transitional shim at
      `src/client/code-pages/SemanticSearch/src/hooks/useDocumentActions.ts`
      (no more local hook — single source of truth in `@spaarke/document-operations`).
    - Deleted obsolete test at
      `src/client/code-pages/SemanticSearch/src/__tests__/hooks/useDocumentActions.test.ts`.
      It mocked the wrong surface (`buildAuthHeaders` + `global.fetch`) while
      the canonical hook uses `authenticatedFetch` from `@spaarke/auth`.
      Was process-crashing on master per W2-031 outcome. Canonical 14-test
      suite at `src/client/shared/Spaarke.DocumentOperations/__tests__/hooks/useDocumentActions.test.tsx`
      provides full behavior coverage. ADR-038 mirror-test ban applies (don't
      duplicate at the consumer when behavior owner has KEEP-path coverage).
    - `package.json` step (POML step 2) was already satisfied — task 031 had
      already added `@spaarke/document-operations` as a file:dependency.

    Verification:
    - SemanticSearch webpack build: clean (0 errors, 3 pre-existing
      bundle-size warnings — unchanged from baseline).
    - SemanticSearch test suite: 20 suites / 423 tests / 319 pass / 104 fail.
      The 104 failures are PRE-EXISTING (verified by stashing all changes and
      re-running — identical failure count). Failures are in `useSavedSearches`,
      `useFilterOptions`, etc. — unrelated to `useDocumentActions`. Net delta
      from this task: -1 test suite (deleted broken file), zero new failures.
    - Hot-path coordination: SpaarkeAi=Y but isolated to SemanticSearch source —
      no conflict with active worktrees.

    Decision deltas vs POML:
    - POML step 1 named `SearchCommandBar.tsx` as the consumer-to-refactor;
      actual consumer is `App.tsx` (SearchCommandBar receives handlers via
      props). POML constraint "find ALL consumers via grep" took precedence.
    - POML did not address the obsolete test file; the dispatch brief did.
      Deletion chosen per ADR-038 (no mirror tests when behavior owner is
      tested) and CLAUDE.md §11 (cost-of-doing-nothing — keeping a broken
      duplicate against a non-existent surface = pure tech debt).

    Quality gates (Step 9.5):
    - code-review: passed (pure import-path refactor; no banned ADR-038
      patterns; comment cites task 031/032 lineage).
    - adr-check: passed (ADR-013 BFF facade respected via canonical hook;
      ADR-028 Auth v2 respected via `authenticatedFetch`; ADR-038 testing
      strategy respected by deleting mirror duplicate).

    Downstream open items:
    - Task 033 (next in Phase 3): Compose adopts the hook via
      `import { useDocumentActions } from '@spaarke/document-operations'`
      with its own `bffBaseUrl` source (likely the SpaarkeAi runtime config).
    - Pre-existing 104 test failures in SemanticSearch suite are technical
      debt not owned by task 032. Recommend separate /defer entry if not
      already tracked.
  </notes>
</task>
